The paper deals with the concept of mutual information, which is a fundamental concept in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a method for mutual information estimation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses copula entropy, which is a statistical measure used in various fields such as signal processing, machine learning, and finance, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI and cs.NE.
